DsmlResponseDocument Class

In this Article

The DsmlResponseDocument class is a read-only collection generated as a response to a DsmlRequestDocument object that contains zero, or more, objects derived from DirectoryResponse.

    public string RequestId { get; }

    Property Value

      The RequestID associated with the document.

    Exceptions

    • NotSupportedException

      You attempted to set the property value.

    Remarks

    This property is read-only and throws an exception if you attempt to set the property value.

  • SyncRoot

    The SyncRoot property contains an object that can be used to synchronize access to the DsmlResponseDocument.

    protected object SyncRoot { get; }

    Property Value

    • Object

      An object that can be used to synchronize access to the DsmlResponseDocument.

    Remarks

    Derived classes can provide synchronized versions of the DsmlResponseDocument using the SyncRoot property. The synchronizing code must perform operations on the SyncRoot of the DsmlResponseDocument, not directly on the DsmlResponseDocument. This ensures proper operation of collections derived from other objects. Specifically, it maintains proper synchronization with other threads that might be simultaneously modifying the DsmlResponseDocument object.

    public void CopyTo (System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryResponse[] value, int i);

    Parameters

    • value
      DirectoryResponse[]

      A one-dimensional array that is the destination of the elements copied from the DsmlRequestDocument object.

    • i
      Int32

      The zero-based index of value where copying begins.

    Exceptions

    • ArgumentNullException

      value is a null reference (Nothing in Visual Basic).

    • ArgumentOutOfRangeException

      i is less than zero.

    • ArgumentException

      value is multidimensional

      -or-

      The number of elements in the source DsmlRequestDocument is greater than the available space from i to the end of the destination value.

    • InvalidCastException

      The type of the source DsmlRequestDocument cannot be cast automatically to the type of the destination value.
